4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, many examining and licensing
6 boards that regulate professions in the State of
7 Alabama accept experience, training, and education
8 gained by an individual during military service as
9 credit toward occupational or professional
10 qualification requirements.
11 This bill would extend this allowance to
12 individuals seeking an emergency medical services
13 personnel license from the Alabama Department of Public
14 Health.
15 This bill would delete duplicative language and
16 also make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update
17 the existing code language to current style.
18
19
20 A BILL
21 TO BE ENTITLED
22 AN ACT
23
24 Relating to emergency medical services personnel; to
25 amend Section 22-18-4, Code of Alabama 1975, to require the
26 Alabama Department of Public Health to credit education or
27 training acquired in military service toward qualifying for an
28 emergency medical services personnel license; and to delete
Page 1

emergency medical services personnel license; and to delete
