29 duplicative language and make nonsubstantive, technical
30 revisions to update the existing code language to current
31 style.
32 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
33 Section 1. Section 22-18-4, Code of Alabama 1975, is
34 amended to read as follows:
35 "§22-18-4
36 (a) In addition to all other fees now payable, the
37 Board of Healthdepartment shall establish, by rule, a fee for
38 EMSP and air or ground provider service licenses. Each license
39 issued to an EMSP shall be valid for a period of 24 calendar
40 months. Each license issued to a provider service shall be
41 valid for a period not to exceed 12 calendar months. The same
42 fee shall be charged for renewal of a license. No additional
43 fee shall be collected when an EMSP becomes eligible for
44 reclassification of his or her license to a higher level.
45 (b) All fees collected under this chapter shall be
46 retained in a separate fund by the Board of Healthdepartment
47 for the purpose of enforcing this chapter, and shall be
48 disbursed as other funds of the state are disbursed; provided,
49 that no fee or permit charge authorized under this chapter
50 shall be charged or collected for the issuing of a permit to a
51 volunteer rescue squad, as defined in Section 32-11-1, for
52 providing ambulance service on a gratuitous basis, or any
53 member thereof who volunteers his or her service, unless
54 licensure is requested by the squad, company, or individual,
55 whereupon, a fee willshall be charged.
56 (c) Any person desiring EMSP licensure shall complete
